this is one of my all time favorites along with the other gidget movies... It was a nice flash of the past in my childhood watching this movie when it aired back in the 70's....
I've loved this movie ever since I first saw it in January 1972. It brings back a lot of memories for me. Thanks for putting it out on DVD. I would like to see Gidget Grows Up on DVD as well.

1972 saw the release of the made for tv film Gidget Gets Married. It starred Monie Ellis, and Michael Burns playing Moondoggie. Joan Bennett provides good support. Gidget fans will be happy with this one. I enjoyed this when it came out, and am happy it is finally available on DVD.
